subSubSection.paragraph:
Puparium
(
Figs 4h–j
). Yellow to brown, surface smooth. Anterior end inflated, posterior 1/3 abruptly flattened and tapering. Anterior 1/2 concave ventrally, posterior 1/2 flattened ventrally (and apparently was the part attached to the substrate). Anterior spiracles not found. Pupal spiracles absent. Posterior respiratory process short, with one pair of longitudinal, oval, spiracular openings anteriorly and two pairs of transversal oval openings posteriorly, these openings with a dark border; with one dark tubercle on the medial side of the anterior opening and two tubercles between the anterior and the posterior opening, the latter tubercles might be distanced (female) or close (male, 
Fig. 4h
) to each other.
